  "prompt": "Which coaching institute is better for cat TIME or IMS?",
  "response": "Both TIME (Triumphant Institute of Management Education) and IMS (Institute of Management Studies) are well-known coaching institutes for CAT (Common Admission Test) preparation. Here's a comparative overview:\n\nTIME:\nPros:\n- Extensive study material\n- Large number of mock tests\n- Comprehensive online and offline coaching\n- Good track record in CAT preparation\n- Strong faculty\n\nIMS:\nPros:\n- Structured study program\n- Good quality mock tests\n- Personalized coaching\n- Strong doubt-clearing sessions\n- Experienced faculty\n\nFactors to consider:\n1. Personal learning style\n2. Location of coaching center\n3. Batch timings\n4. Faculty quality in your specific center\n5. Cost of the program\n6. Past performance of the coaching center\n\nRecommendation:\n- Both are good institutes\n- Visit local centers\n- Attend demo classes\n- Talk to current/previous students\n- Choose based on personal comfort and learning preferences\n\nUltimately, individual effort and dedication matter more than the coaching institute. Select the one that suits your learning style and provides a comfortable learning environment.",
